1
00:00:06,150 --> 00:00:08,150
[disquieting music plays]

2
00:00:18,550 --> 00:00:19,950
[footfalls echo ominously]

3
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:28,230
[Mr. Phillips] Save me, O God, 
for the waters have come up to my neck.

4
00:00:28,310 --> 00:00:30,710
I sink in the miry depths.

5
00:00:31,950 --> 00:00:34,230
The floods engulf me.

6
00:00:35,230 --> 00:00:37,030
[Mrs. Phillips] Evil exists, Rosie.

7
00:00:37,830 --> 00:00:39,390
We must live our beliefs.

8
00:00:39,470 --> 00:00:41,950
[congregation] Repent! Repent!

9
00:00:42,030 --> 00:00:44,390
- [Rosie gasps]
- Repent! Repent! Repent!

10
00:00:44,470 --> 00:00:45,670
[gasps]

11
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:48,630
[birds chirp pleasantly]

12
00:00:48,710 --> 00:00:51,430
[breathes heavily]

13
00:01:07,910 --> 00:01:09,070
[door opens distantly]

14
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:11,510
[midwife] Rosie, it's time.

15
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:14,510
[somber theme music plays]

16
00:01:21,590 --> 00:01:23,910
[Hannah grunting]

17
00:01:32,510 --> 00:01:34,110
[groans]

18
00:01:34,190 --> 00:01:35,750
[continues grunting]

19
00:01:35,830 --> 00:01:36,910
[Mrs. Phillips] How's Grace?

20
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:39,190
All right. Yeah, she's fine.

21
00:01:39,270 --> 00:01:42,310
Five minutes apart.
There's a way to go yet.

22
00:01:42,390 --> 00:01:43,950
Maybe.

23
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:46,870
They seem to get faster every baby.

24
00:01:48,430 --> 00:01:49,910
Thank you for helping.

25
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:53,150
I know it's not easy for you.

26
00:01:53,230 --> 00:01:54,550
I'm happy to.

27
00:01:55,470 --> 00:01:56,470
[sighs]

28
00:01:57,630 --> 00:02:00,430
- Wait in hope for the Lord, Rosie.
- Amen.

29
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:04,950
Why don't you go
and make the children some breakfast?

30
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:08,430
[Hannah continues groaning]

31
00:02:08,509 --> 00:02:10,509
[gentle somber music plays]

32
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:13,470
[Hannah grunting]

33
00:02:21,670 --> 00:02:24,070
[Adam] By the time
you're back from school, 

34
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:25,870
you're gonna have a new cousin.

35
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:29,070
Uncle Isaac said I can have first cuddle.

36
00:02:30,470 --> 00:02:31,470
Toast or cereal?

37
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:33,950
Egg on toast, like Mummy makes.

38
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,870
[knocking at window]

39
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:39,110
[Mr. Phillips] Brother Adam.

40
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:42,270
Grace, would you be a big girl
and pop to the shed

41
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:44,230
and get some eggs for yourself, yeah?

42
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:45,710
[chickens cluck]

43
00:03:05,470 --> 00:03:08,070
♪ One, two, buckle my shoe ♪

44
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:11,110
♪ Three, four, he's knocking at the door ♪

45
00:03:16,390 --> 00:03:18,990
♪ Five, six, he never plays-- ♪

46
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:20,150
[Sam] Hello, Grace.

47
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:23,190
It's okay. [chuckles softly]

48
00:03:25,390 --> 00:03:26,590
It's just me.

49
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,750
Sam.

50
00:03:30,390 --> 00:03:31,470
From the river.

51
00:03:32,390 --> 00:03:33,590
Do you remember?

52
00:03:35,790 --> 00:03:37,070
Is that breakfast?

53
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:39,950
What'll you have?

54
00:03:40,550 --> 00:03:42,110
Scrambled? Fried?

55
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:44,790
I-- I shouldn't be talking to you.

56
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:47,590
You're an unchosen.

57
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,150
What's an unchosen?

58
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,070
You are.

59
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:53,190
So I can't be your friend, 

60
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:55,350
can't play music, 

61
00:03:55,430 --> 00:03:57,350
and I can't cut my hair.

62
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:58,470
[Sam sighs]

63
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:00,990
Lots of rules.

64
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:04,390
They keep me safe from the devil.

65
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,510
What's that?

66
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:11,750
This is a corn dolly.

67
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:15,430
I used to make these all the time
when I was your age.

68
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:18,670
You can have it if you want.

69
00:04:21,029 --> 00:04:22,910
Something to remember me by.

70
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,350
Keep it in your pocket.

71
00:04:35,710 --> 00:04:39,390
♪ Three, four, knocking on the door ♪

72
00:04:40,670 --> 00:04:41,830
[Adam] The Great Leader?

73
00:04:41,910 --> 00:04:45,110
How the secular authorities dare
to question his tax affairs…

74
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:46,150
And obviously, uh, 

75
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:50,590
Mr. Crane's financial expertise, 
much needed in Canada.

76
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:51,790
So…

77
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:54,750
an opportunity, Adam.

78
00:04:57,550 --> 00:04:58,670
Sorry, I don't follow.

79
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:00,630
A leadership role.

80
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:03,670
Probationary period.

81
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:05,270
[Adam exhales]

82
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:07,830
Goodness. I…

83
00:05:07,910 --> 00:05:08,990
I, uh…

84
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:12,550
Thank you.

85
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:14,070
It's much deserved.

86
00:05:14,150 --> 00:05:17,310
You put us first. Before your own brother.

87
00:05:18,470 --> 00:05:21,310
Disciplinary matters, family members.

88
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,950
Our greatest challenge.

89
00:05:27,590 --> 00:05:28,670
I'm honored

90
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,430
to take up this mantle.

91
00:05:32,550 --> 00:05:34,470
I know it's not
what you would have wanted.

92
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:38,230
You will make a good shepherd.

93
00:05:39,710 --> 00:05:41,150
[solemn music plays]

94
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:44,230
But now…

95
00:05:46,270 --> 00:05:47,830
a big day.

96
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:53,550
No greater job than to save a man's soul.

97
00:05:55,790 --> 00:05:56,830
[sighs]

98
00:05:58,710 --> 00:05:59,830
[door closes]

99
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:04,750
[Rosie] Anthony, 
what does your dad prefer?

100
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:06,390
Honey or Marmite?

101
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:09,630
Don't know.

102
00:06:12,710 --> 00:06:14,270
Okay, we'll go with honey.

103
00:06:19,230 --> 00:06:20,790
Why don't you take this up to him?

104
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:26,870
Don't want to.

105
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:32,030
Don't want to be tainted.

106
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:39,070
Anthony, I know you must be scared, 

107
00:06:39,150 --> 00:06:42,350
but… Daddy's just broken a rule.

108
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,550
That's all.

109
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:46,990
Aunt Rosie?

110
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:48,030
Yeah.

111
00:06:48,990 --> 00:06:50,870
[softly] Do you ever break the rules?

112
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:55,950
[ominous music plays]

113
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:09,150
Hey.

114
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:11,230
Hey, Rosie. Please, you need to help me.

115
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,590
Just call this number.

116
00:07:14,190 --> 00:07:15,150
What is it?

117
00:07:15,230 --> 00:07:17,550
It's, uh, just a friend. Uh, Charley.

118
00:07:17,630 --> 00:07:19,430
They'll be worried. Please.

119
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:22,110
- I can't do that.
- Please.

120
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,510
- [knocking]
- [Grace] Mummy.

121
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:26,430
- Where's the baby?
- Rosie, thank you.

122
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:30,510
[lock clicks]

123
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:33,070
[door opens]

124
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:35,390
- [Hannah groans]
- Hey.

125
00:07:35,470 --> 00:07:37,470
- All's well?
- Yeah, she's okay.

126
00:07:37,550 --> 00:07:39,430
Mummy, corn dolly.

127
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:40,870
The man made it for me.

128
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:43,110
[ominous music intensifies]

129
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:46,910
What man?

130
00:07:49,350 --> 00:07:51,190
- The man from--
- Isaac gave me this.

131
00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:53,670
Told me to ring Charley.

132
00:07:55,870 --> 00:07:57,030
Who is he?

133
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:04,350
"She."

134
00:08:05,430 --> 00:08:06,710
Charley's a woman.

135
00:08:07,990 --> 00:08:09,270
Unchosen.

136
00:08:09,950 --> 00:08:13,070
Rosie, whatever happens here today, 
I have to prove myself.

137
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:14,470
- To who?
- [vehicle approaches]

138
00:08:14,550 --> 00:08:15,710
To God.

139
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:19,230
- He must know I'm worthy.
- [vehicle doors close]

140
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:21,310
[men chatter indistinctly]

141
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:25,230
Sister Amy will take Grace
and her cousins to school.

142
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:28,110
Anthony stays here with the men.

143
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:30,230
[tense music plays]

144
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:34,630
[Adam] Mr. Phillips, my brother's sin
is worse than I first thought.

145
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:49,630
[uneasy ethereal music plays]

146
00:08:54,990 --> 00:08:57,310
[Adam] We're not here
to punish you, brother.

147
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:59,510
Or humiliate you.

148
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,950
But to bring you back to the Lord.

149
00:09:06,310 --> 00:09:07,950
It's just a phone, Adam.

150
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:12,910
But it's more than that, isn't it?

151
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:15,710
No, Adam. Adam, no, hey.

152
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,990
Adam, please, no.

153
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:22,270
- This is for your own good.
- [liquid pours]

154
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,510
No. No, I don't want it, Adam, please.

155
00:09:25,590 --> 00:09:27,590
[uneasy music intensifies]

156
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:29,270
- Drink it, brother.
- No, I don't want it.

157
00:09:29,350 --> 00:09:31,190
Drink it! And listen to me.

158
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:34,990
You are living in sin.

159
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:38,830
Adulterous, lustful sin.

160
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:43,750
[midwife] Rosie, come now. Come away.

161
00:09:43,830 --> 00:09:45,670
Let the men do their work.

162
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:49,150
Keep going.

163
00:09:51,430 --> 00:09:52,670
[groans]

164
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:55,390
Here, take a breath. That's it.

165
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:58,630
[groans]

166
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:01,270
That's it, honey. Keep going.

167
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:02,590
[groans heavily]

168
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:05,390
[uneasy ethereal music continues playing]

169
00:10:06,430 --> 00:10:07,390
[winces]

170
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:09,630
You betray your faith.

171
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:11,070
[swallows and exhales]

172
00:10:12,910 --> 00:10:13,750
And your wife.

173
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,830
And your family.

174
00:10:18,350 --> 00:10:19,310
More.

175
00:10:21,670 --> 00:10:23,550
No. No.

176
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:36,870
Ugh.

177
00:10:41,310 --> 00:10:42,790
Fight this.

178
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,390
Just fight this demon.

179
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:46,030
Hey, you fight it.

180
00:10:46,990 --> 00:10:48,270
And you defeat it.

181
00:10:49,110 --> 00:10:51,990
You will prove to Jesus
you are worthy of heaven.

182
00:10:52,070 --> 00:10:52,910
Yeah.

183
00:10:58,110 --> 00:10:59,230
Repent.

184
00:10:59,310 --> 00:11:01,990
[men] Repent! Repent!

185
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:04,590
- [Hannah groans]
- Repent! Repent!

186
00:11:05,310 --> 00:11:09,030
Repent! Repent! Repent!

187
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:11,790
- I need to go.
- [Mrs. Phillips] Rosie?

188
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:14,390
[Rosie] I need some air.

189
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,910
[suspenseful classical music plays]

190
00:11:26,950 --> 00:11:28,110
[music swells and stops]

191
00:11:42,590 --> 00:11:43,670
[sighs softly]

192
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:45,630
[intriguing musical flourish plays]

193
00:11:53,190 --> 00:11:55,190
[tense brooding music plays]

194
00:11:59,630 --> 00:12:00,750
[lock clicks]

195
00:12:35,830 --> 00:12:37,310
[Adam] This sickness…

196
00:12:39,430 --> 00:12:40,630
Let us help you.

197
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:45,710
Dr. Bailey can free you

198
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:47,550
from this unhealthy passion.

199
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,270
[Isaac] How will a doctor help?

200
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:53,350
[slurring] There isn't a pill
that'll change how I feel.

201
00:12:54,070 --> 00:12:57,190
Adam, please.
Please, why are you doing this to me?

202
00:12:57,270 --> 00:13:01,590
You are in the grip
of an ungodly perversion.

203
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:02,670
[scoffs]

204
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:05,550
And you'd know all about that, 
hey, brother?

205
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:09,910
[melancholic music plays]

206
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:13,110
No! No, no… [mutters]

207
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:16,870
[Isaac gags]

208
00:13:19,790 --> 00:13:21,710
[splutters and coughs]

209
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:24,310
No, no, no! No.

210
00:13:25,390 --> 00:13:29,150
[spits] No! No, no.

211
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:32,150
[thuds]

212
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:35,630
- Sit down.
- No.

213
00:13:35,710 --> 00:13:38,270
- Sit down!
- No, I'm not going to do this, okay?

214
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:39,310
Sit down.

215
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,870
No, I am sorry
for what I've done to Hannah.

216
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:45,470
Okay? No, I am sorry
for what I've done to Hannah.

217
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:47,270
- I truly wish I could love her.
- Sit down!

218
00:13:47,350 --> 00:13:49,350
I truly tried to love her.

219
00:13:50,310 --> 00:13:51,270
But I don't.

220
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:53,830
God knows I tried. I didn't look for love.

221
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:55,870
But yes, I found love elsewhere.

222
00:13:55,950 --> 00:13:57,590
That doesn't make me a pervert!

223
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,510
That doesn't make me a pervert!

224
00:14:12,350 --> 00:14:14,550
No. No, Adam, please.

225
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,990
Not this. Anything else.

226
00:14:16,070 --> 00:14:17,790
Don't use my boy against me, Adam.

227
00:14:17,870 --> 00:14:18,910
Please.

228
00:14:19,590 --> 00:14:21,590
[somber ethereal music plays]

229
00:14:24,350 --> 00:14:26,190
Anthony. Hey.

230
00:14:26,830 --> 00:14:29,550
Anthony, look at me.
I'm here. Hey, I'm here.

231
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:31,750
I'm sorry, okay?

232
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:33,190
Hey, Daddy's here.

233
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:34,990
Daddy's here.

234
00:14:35,590 --> 00:14:36,430
Please.

235
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,590
- [winces sadly]
- Devil.

236
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:03,710
[inaudible]

237
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:05,470
[somber ethereal music continues]

238
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:06,590
[whimpers]

239
00:15:08,150 --> 00:15:09,670
[yells]

240
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:10,830
[baby crying]

241
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,550
[music turns hopeful and serene]

242
00:15:12,630 --> 00:15:14,710
[Hannah groans]

243
00:15:15,710 --> 00:15:16,670
[midwife] Here.

244
00:15:17,670 --> 00:15:18,870
[Hannah chuckles softly]

245
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:22,510
- [laughing] Blessed be the child.
- Oh, hello.

246
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:25,070
Here. [laughs]

247
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:28,070
- You're okay. Come on.
- [midwife] There.

248
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:29,910
- [baby cries]
- Oh, I know.

249
00:15:29,990 --> 00:15:32,270
- [Mrs. Phillips] Aw!
- [midwife] Beautiful baby boy.

250
00:15:32,350 --> 00:15:35,150
[sighs and laughs]

251
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:38,110
[Mrs. Phillips] A chosen one.

252
00:15:45,430 --> 00:15:46,350
[Mr. Phillips] Get up!

253
00:15:46,430 --> 00:15:47,590
- [struggling]
- [Adam] In there.

254
00:15:48,710 --> 00:15:49,670
[Isaac grunts]

255
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:53,750
[man] Come on.

256
00:15:54,710 --> 00:15:55,950
- [Hannah chuckles]
- [baby cries]

257
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,270
Come on in, Rosie.

258
00:16:00,270 --> 00:16:02,750
Oh! [laughs]

259
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:05,430
Ooh! Beautiful little child.

260
00:16:06,230 --> 00:16:08,190
[Hannah] I'm so proud of you.

261
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:10,870
I heard you did brilliantly downstairs.

262
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,310
And you needn't worry.

263
00:16:12,390 --> 00:16:14,950
We won't let Daddy
see the baby until he's all better.

264
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:18,430
We need to keep baby Noah safe.

265
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,150
And you mustn't worry either.

266
00:16:21,070 --> 00:16:23,630
No matter what happens, 
we'll look after you.

267
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:27,070
Much easier now with Adam.

268
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:29,990
Are you excited, Rosie? The news?

269
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:32,350
Sorry?

270
00:16:32,430 --> 00:16:33,870
Adam's been made an elder.

271
00:16:35,190 --> 00:16:36,630
Right.

272
00:16:38,990 --> 00:16:42,270
Come on, Anthony.
Let's give your mum some peace.

273
00:16:43,710 --> 00:16:45,710
[footsteps recede into distance]

274
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:48,990
- [door closes]
- [baby coos]

275
00:16:49,590 --> 00:16:50,710
Congratulations.

276
00:16:51,470 --> 00:16:52,790
I never asked for this.

277
00:16:52,870 --> 00:16:56,150
No? It seems some people
don't have to do much.

278
00:16:56,230 --> 00:16:58,070
Still climb the ladder.

279
00:17:01,470 --> 00:17:02,790
I-I'm sorry about Isaac.

280
00:17:03,430 --> 00:17:05,349
- [sniffles]
- About all of this.

281
00:17:05,430 --> 00:17:08,470
But it doesn't make a difference
if Adam's an elder or not.

282
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:09,390
I'll always help.

283
00:17:09,470 --> 00:17:10,710
'Course you will.

284
00:17:11,910 --> 00:17:13,069
[breath trembles]

285
00:17:14,430 --> 00:17:17,310
[sarcastically] Aunt Rosie, the saint.

286
00:17:22,030 --> 00:17:23,710
[melancholic music plays]

287
00:17:23,790 --> 00:17:25,069
[midwife] You know that…

288
00:17:25,829 --> 00:17:27,430
Isaac's pain…

289
00:17:28,870 --> 00:17:32,470
it's nothing compared
to the torment of eternal damnation.

290
00:17:33,510 --> 00:17:35,990
Our suffering brings us closer to God.

291
00:17:37,710 --> 00:17:40,190
But where is the love in all of this, Mum?

292
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:43,830
You always taught me Jesus is love.

293
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:48,110
And… love comes in-- in different ways.

294
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:52,550
[gently] Hey.

295
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:08,790
[faucet squeaks, water stops]

296
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:11,790
[glasses clatter softly]

297
00:18:14,830 --> 00:18:16,110
Put your trust in the Lord…

298
00:18:18,630 --> 00:18:20,630
and the men who follow his instructions.

299
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:23,550
Mr. Phillips, Adam.

300
00:18:24,390 --> 00:18:25,750
Their rules.

301
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:28,830
Regulations are the word of God.

302
00:18:33,150 --> 00:18:35,470
Even when the heart says otherwise.

303
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:43,470
What are you doing?

304
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:46,310
- Mr. Phillips said--
- No!

305
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:48,070
No, don't drink that.

306
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:51,430
- Go play with your cars.
- [liquid pours]

307
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:58,590
[Mrs. Phillips] Sit down, Anthony.

308
00:18:59,110 --> 00:18:59,990
Come on.

309
00:19:01,550 --> 00:19:03,030
- Here you go.
- Mmm.

310
00:19:03,870 --> 00:19:04,870
Right.

311
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:08,310
That's a fancy one. Big wheels.

312
00:19:08,390 --> 00:19:11,110
- Which is your favorite? Blue one?
- [Anthony] Mm-hmm. Yeah, yeah.

313
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:15,390
Do you ever think about him?

314
00:19:17,710 --> 00:19:18,710
Your son?

315
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:23,110
No.

316
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:27,110
[ominous music plays]

317
00:19:27,190 --> 00:19:28,390
[hands immerse in water]

318
00:19:32,430 --> 00:19:34,310
[Rosie scrubs laundry]

319
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:40,830
[switch flicks heavily]

320
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:03,710
[ominous music intensifies]

321
00:20:39,470 --> 00:20:40,990
[tender music plays]

322
00:20:55,710 --> 00:20:57,710
[chattering indistinctly]

323
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:22,670
[brakes squeal gently]

324
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:24,070
[door slides open]

325
00:21:25,950 --> 00:21:28,630
- Mummy!
- Hey, chickpea! Oh.

326
00:21:28,710 --> 00:21:30,310
[telephone ringing]

327
00:21:41,350 --> 00:21:42,190
Hello?

328
00:21:42,270 --> 00:21:43,750
[man] Is Sam there?

329
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:46,150
He-- He called me from this number.

330
00:21:47,910 --> 00:21:49,670
- Who's this?
- It's Mason.

331
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:51,590
Look, I-- I need to speak with him.

332
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:55,950
Tell him the police are looking for him.
It's all kicking off over here.

333
00:21:56,030 --> 00:21:57,350
Sam's not here.

334
00:21:57,430 --> 00:21:58,950
Don't call here again.

335
00:21:59,030 --> 00:22:01,030
- [tense music plays]
- [phone beeps]

336
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:21,310
[gasps]

337
00:22:26,110 --> 00:22:27,870
- [keys jingle and fall]
- Fuck.

338
00:22:29,030 --> 00:22:30,150
[door opens]

339
00:22:30,230 --> 00:22:31,150
[grunts]

340
00:22:32,990 --> 00:22:34,030
[engine starts]

341
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:36,630
[engine revs, tires squeal]

342
00:22:45,910 --> 00:22:47,910
[cries softly]

343
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:53,030
[Rosie] Do you want me
to take him for a bit?

344
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:56,510
[continues crying]

345
00:22:56,590 --> 00:22:59,510
Yeah, I know. I know.

346
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:02,030
It's okay. Let's go on a walk.

347
00:23:03,030 --> 00:23:06,110
Let's go. Let's go.

348
00:23:11,550 --> 00:23:12,590
[Noah coos]

349
00:23:23,750 --> 00:23:24,750
[softly] Isaac.

350
00:23:26,150 --> 00:23:27,070
[Noah coos]

351
00:23:32,030 --> 00:23:34,870
I'm sorry, I shouldn't
have given Adam your note.

352
00:23:38,150 --> 00:23:39,270
The baby…

353
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:41,910
what did she have?

354
00:23:49,190 --> 00:23:50,550
[lock rattles]

355
00:23:58,470 --> 00:23:59,670
This is Noah.

356
00:24:01,830 --> 00:24:03,350
[tender music plays]

357
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:16,950
[Hannah groans in distance]

358
00:24:19,910 --> 00:24:22,510
[Noah cries softly]

359
00:24:25,870 --> 00:24:27,110
Hello, Noah.

360
00:24:28,430 --> 00:24:29,590
Are you okay?

361
00:24:31,430 --> 00:24:33,870
[sighs] So peaceful.

362
00:24:34,990 --> 00:24:37,110
I love you, Noah. Hmm?

363
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:40,910
My baby boy. [chuckles]

364
00:24:41,910 --> 00:24:43,790
[sighs] My baby boy.

365
00:24:55,950 --> 00:24:58,750
Rosie, you know I love
all my children, right?

366
00:25:02,030 --> 00:25:03,550
But I can't stay here anymore.

367
00:25:04,430 --> 00:25:06,750
- What?
- I need to go tonight.

368
00:25:07,270 --> 00:25:08,430
During the meeting.

369
00:25:09,470 --> 00:25:11,230
Will you help me, please?

370
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:15,030
I can't. They'll notice that I'm gone.

371
00:25:15,110 --> 00:25:18,870
Rosie. Rosie, we have time, okay?
You'll be fine. Please.

372
00:25:19,430 --> 00:25:20,590
Please, I'm begging you.

373
00:25:21,190 --> 00:25:25,150
Just get me Adam's van keys, 
and I'll do the rest, okay?

374
00:25:25,670 --> 00:25:27,030
[chickens cluck]

375
00:25:29,350 --> 00:25:31,350
[dishes clatter softly]

376
00:25:32,790 --> 00:25:34,190
Your crackling…

377
00:25:34,830 --> 00:25:36,910
nothing short of spectacular.

378
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:39,390
Thank you.

379
00:25:39,910 --> 00:25:42,950
Organic pork. Not cheap, but…

380
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:45,230
Shouldn't be a problem soon.

381
00:25:46,470 --> 00:25:48,830
Busy year for Harrison's Sawmill.

382
00:25:48,910 --> 00:25:51,510
The Fellowship secured the land
for the new school.

383
00:25:51,590 --> 00:25:53,990
And we've been asked
to provide the timber.

384
00:25:54,070 --> 00:25:55,830
[Mr. Phillips] A significant contract.

385
00:25:55,910 --> 00:25:57,950
And we are very grateful.

386
00:25:58,030 --> 00:25:59,230
We are.

387
00:26:02,590 --> 00:26:03,790
[wine pours]

388
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:10,270
May the Lord bring
blessings on our wealth.

389
00:26:11,510 --> 00:26:13,190
- Amen.
- [Adam and Mrs. Phillips] Amen.

390
00:26:14,390 --> 00:26:16,390
[menacing music plays]

391
00:26:17,030 --> 00:26:18,630
[Mr. Phillips] We'll try again tomorrow.

392
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:21,590
Bring your brother back, 
turn him from his wrongdoing.

393
00:26:21,670 --> 00:26:24,510
I will bring him to repentance.
My brother will stay in the fold.

394
00:26:24,590 --> 00:26:26,350
- Do you need help?
- No, you're fine, honestly.

395
00:26:26,430 --> 00:26:30,110
[Mr. Phillips] Bailey will administer
the bromide. Calm him down.

396
00:26:30,830 --> 00:26:32,790
Suppress his urges.

397
00:26:32,870 --> 00:26:35,070
[Adam] I'll make
the necessary arrangements.

398
00:26:36,790 --> 00:26:38,470
[men continue indistinctly]

399
00:26:41,470 --> 00:26:43,470
[menacing music intensifies]

400
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:58,470
Rosie, dear, I wish you'd talk to my wife.

401
00:26:58,550 --> 00:27:00,670
She could learn a thing or two from you.

402
00:27:01,230 --> 00:27:03,270
- I'm sorry?
- The gravy.

403
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:06,910
Delicious. You should give her the recipe.

404
00:27:07,710 --> 00:27:08,830
Rosie.

405
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:22,070
Always a pleasure cooking for you.
Time for dessert.

406
00:27:22,710 --> 00:27:25,670
Better be quick.
Get ready for the meeting.

407
00:27:30,670 --> 00:27:32,870
[congregation applauds]

408
00:27:32,950 --> 00:27:35,950
- Hallelujah!
- [all] Hallelujah!

409
00:27:36,030 --> 00:27:38,510
And as we welcome Adam into his new role, 

410
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:41,670
we bid farewell to Mr. Crane.

411
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:44,990
Wish him well with his relocation.

412
00:27:45,510 --> 00:27:47,430
Canada's gain is our loss.

413
00:27:57,630 --> 00:28:00,070
Thank you, Mr. Phillips.

414
00:28:02,750 --> 00:28:05,950
What an honor it is to be standing here, 

415
00:28:06,750 --> 00:28:08,030
in front of you all, 

416
00:28:08,670 --> 00:28:09,830
in this room, 

417
00:28:10,430 --> 00:28:11,750
to lead you in prayer.

418
00:28:14,670 --> 00:28:17,470
Dear Lord, we ask for your divine help

419
00:28:17,550 --> 00:28:21,310
to stay on the righteous path
you have set out for us.

420
00:28:21,390 --> 00:28:24,070
To help us remember
that your word is the lamp

421
00:28:24,150 --> 00:28:26,910
which guides us through this world
and into the next.

422
00:28:27,630 --> 00:28:32,670
We put our trust in you
and your unending love and grace.

423
00:28:32,750 --> 00:28:34,870
- Amen.
- [all] Amen.

424
00:28:34,950 --> 00:28:36,390
[tense ethereal music plays]

425
00:28:39,070 --> 00:28:40,510
As you well know, 

426
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:44,550
I've been wrestling
with the pain of sin within my own family.

427
00:28:46,030 --> 00:28:47,030
My own brother.

428
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:50,550
But even in suffering, there is joy.

429
00:28:50,630 --> 00:28:54,030
For today, our sister Hannah
has given birth to a son.

430
00:28:54,790 --> 00:28:57,070
- Hallelujah.
- [all] Hallelujah.

431
00:28:57,150 --> 00:29:00,030
- And we welcome baby Noah into our family.
- [mock sighs]

432
00:29:00,950 --> 00:29:03,190
And we bless sister Hannah.

433
00:29:03,270 --> 00:29:05,190
It's truly a fruitful vine.

434
00:29:05,270 --> 00:29:06,270
Why me?

435
00:29:07,590 --> 00:29:09,950
Why am I the one with an only child?

436
00:29:10,510 --> 00:29:13,510
Don't say "only."
Every child is a blessing.

437
00:29:14,390 --> 00:29:15,430
[sighs]

438
00:29:17,350 --> 00:29:19,350
Do you need to go out, take a breather?

439
00:29:19,430 --> 00:29:21,110
No. I can't.

440
00:29:22,550 --> 00:29:25,230
You can. We'll look after Grace.
Go on, go.

441
00:29:26,070 --> 00:29:27,150
Thank you.

442
00:29:27,230 --> 00:29:28,550
[Adam] …you shall be happy.

443
00:29:29,150 --> 00:29:30,830
And it shall be well with you.

444
00:29:30,910 --> 00:29:32,390
[mouths] It's okay.

445
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:34,470
[dramatic music plays]

446
00:29:35,750 --> 00:29:36,990
[panting]

447
00:29:58,670 --> 00:30:00,030
[lock clicks]

448
00:30:00,110 --> 00:30:01,910
[music swells]

449
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:07,990
[music stops]

450
00:30:08,070 --> 00:30:09,310
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

451
00:30:09,390 --> 00:30:10,710
[baby cries]

452
00:30:13,910 --> 00:30:14,950
[lock clicks]

453
00:30:16,230 --> 00:30:18,750
- [key clatters softly]
- If you're going to go, it has to be now.

454
00:30:19,470 --> 00:30:21,350
They're already breaking bread.

455
00:30:21,430 --> 00:30:22,310
Let's go.

456
00:30:22,390 --> 00:30:24,710
[suspenseful music plays]

457
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:38,710
Thank you for getting these.

458
00:30:38,790 --> 00:30:39,830
I'll miss you.

459
00:30:40,950 --> 00:30:42,150
[van doors unlock]

460
00:30:43,950 --> 00:30:45,470
[Isaac retches]

461
00:30:48,990 --> 00:30:50,270
[groans]

462
00:30:53,350 --> 00:30:54,670
Oh, the whiskey.

463
00:30:55,910 --> 00:30:57,750
You can't drive, not like that.

464
00:30:58,510 --> 00:30:59,350
Can you drive me?

465
00:30:59,430 --> 00:31:01,110
- [door opens]
- No.

466
00:31:02,550 --> 00:31:05,190
No! I never agreed to do that.

467
00:31:05,270 --> 00:31:06,750
No, but you can drive, right?

468
00:31:08,630 --> 00:31:09,670
[door closes]

469
00:31:11,110 --> 00:31:12,670
- [tires squeal]
- [glass shatters]

470
00:31:17,270 --> 00:31:20,430
[Adam] Do you suppose that these Galileans
were worse sinners than other Galileans

471
00:31:20,510 --> 00:31:21,950
because of what they had suffered?

472
00:31:22,030 --> 00:31:23,430
I tell you, no!

473
00:31:24,190 --> 00:31:26,070
Or you will likewise perish.

474
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:29,830
And in Jerusalem, do you think these men, 

475
00:31:29,910 --> 00:31:32,790
they killed at Siloam
by this falling tower, 

476
00:31:32,870 --> 00:31:35,470
they had suffered more than others
who dwelt in Jerusalem?

477
00:31:35,550 --> 00:31:36,910
[horns honk]

478
00:31:36,990 --> 00:31:39,350
You've never been into town
at night, have you?

479
00:31:39,430 --> 00:31:40,550
[siren wails]

480
00:31:41,670 --> 00:31:44,710
You know, they tell us
the outside world's a dangerous place, 

481
00:31:44,790 --> 00:31:46,230
full of misery and evil.

482
00:31:47,070 --> 00:31:47,950
It's not true.

483
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:50,870
They want to keep us
all trapped in fear, Rosie.

484
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:54,910
All the things they deny us, 
they're not sins.

485
00:31:54,990 --> 00:31:55,830
They're just life.

486
00:31:55,910 --> 00:31:58,270
[Adam] And Jesus answered
and said to them, 

487
00:31:58,350 --> 00:32:02,630
"There were present at that season
some who told him about the Galileans, 

488
00:32:02,710 --> 00:32:05,710
whose blood Pilate had mingled
with their sacrifices."

489
00:32:06,950 --> 00:32:09,070
- Amen.
- [all] Amen.

490
00:32:09,150 --> 00:32:11,670
[Isaac] Yeah, this is it.
This is Charley's.

491
00:32:15,310 --> 00:32:17,430
- [parking brake cranks]
- [engine turns off]

492
00:32:21,870 --> 00:32:22,830
Isaac…

493
00:32:23,710 --> 00:32:25,510
God still loves you.

494
00:32:25,590 --> 00:32:28,950
It isn't about God, Rosie.
It's what they do in His name.

495
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:33,550
Adam will silence me for weeks, months.
Try to keep me in the fold.

496
00:32:33,630 --> 00:32:34,710
Can't do that.

497
00:32:35,230 --> 00:32:37,590
Not to myself. And not to my kids.

498
00:32:37,670 --> 00:32:38,990
They won't let you see them.

499
00:32:39,070 --> 00:32:40,470
- I'll make it work.
- How?

500
00:32:40,550 --> 00:32:44,230
Rosie, I have to tell myself that, okay?
Otherwise, I can't do this.

501
00:32:47,350 --> 00:32:48,470
[sighs softly]

502
00:32:49,350 --> 00:32:50,310
Look, thank you.

503
00:32:51,790 --> 00:32:52,910
Thank you for helping me.

504
00:32:56,470 --> 00:32:57,470
[seat belt clicks]

505
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:02,710
I'll miss you, Rosie.

506
00:33:10,110 --> 00:33:11,230
[sighs]

507
00:33:12,990 --> 00:33:14,710
[bittersweet music plays]

508
00:33:16,550 --> 00:33:18,470
[both exclaim happily]

509
00:33:32,190 --> 00:33:34,350
[breath trembles]

510
00:33:35,750 --> 00:33:36,670
[Rosie gasps]

511
00:33:36,750 --> 00:33:38,750
Have you got any spare change, 
please, love?

512
00:33:38,830 --> 00:33:39,790
What?

513
00:33:40,470 --> 00:33:42,390
Have you got any change, please?

514
00:33:42,470 --> 00:33:43,390
Oh, fuck you.

515
00:33:43,470 --> 00:33:45,190
[whimpers]

516
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:53,550
[sighs]

517
00:33:56,350 --> 00:33:57,750
[gasps]

518
00:33:58,630 --> 00:34:01,750
Give me the keys
and get out of the van, Rosie.

519
00:34:04,350 --> 00:34:06,670
All right, don't draw
any attention to yourself.

520
00:34:07,990 --> 00:34:09,790
[siren approaches]

521
00:34:11,110 --> 00:34:12,350
Fuck's sake.

522
00:34:15,790 --> 00:34:18,989
- [second siren approaches]
- Okay, just-- just, uh-- just drive.

523
00:34:24,750 --> 00:34:26,469
[siren whoops nearby]

524
00:34:26,550 --> 00:34:28,429
- Come on! Drive!
- [seat belt clicks]

525
00:34:29,870 --> 00:34:32,510
[men yell in apartment]

526
00:34:36,550 --> 00:34:38,550
[tense pulsing music plays]

527
00:34:51,630 --> 00:34:52,989
[Sam] Stop the van.

528
00:34:57,070 --> 00:34:58,230
[engine idling]

529
00:35:03,190 --> 00:35:05,350
Look, I'm not gonna hurt you, okay?

530
00:35:06,550 --> 00:35:08,190
I just need you to get out.

531
00:35:12,310 --> 00:35:14,350
Did you not hear me? Get out of the van.

532
00:35:14,950 --> 00:35:17,230
You can't just leave me here.
I have to get back.

533
00:35:17,310 --> 00:35:19,470
And I need the fucking van, okay?

534
00:35:19,550 --> 00:35:21,510
Look, you don't understand
what they'll do to me.

535
00:35:22,110 --> 00:35:23,830
Isaac, my brother-in-law, 
I helped him leave.

536
00:35:23,910 --> 00:35:26,750
If they find out, they'll lock me up.
They'll take Grace.

537
